      "Description": "This lesson explores the growing use of artificial intelligence tools in investment analysis and why a cautious, questioning approach is essential for anyone relying on AI-generated insights. You will learn how AI systems can produce confident-sounding recommendations that may be based on outdated data, flawed assumptions, or incomplete market information. We will look at practical ways to verify AI outputs before acting on them, helping you build a habit of critical thinking rather than blind trust. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of where AI can genuinely support your investment research and where human judgement remains indispensable.",
